<font color="#FF0000">PATCHING THE PATCH</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jan 25 13:21:36 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
According to the news this morning there is serious speculation that Mr. Clinton's days are few and numbered.<br>
I hesitate to applaud and celebrate his demise because of  greater concerns.  <br>
Respect for the Office of the President is an essential element. If we, as a gathering of people, are to make democracy work... serve it up as a show case to the world.. then it must be wrapped in dignity and values shared by all people, worldwide.  The American voters.. with their power to choose their leaders must suffer the humiliation that comes when they make poor or uneducated choices.  We can no longer elect leaders because of advertizing ploys and hype. I feel that politicians should no longer be choosen because of the color of their ties or the size of their campaign funds.<br>
Being politically correct should be overhauled to become factually correct.  Individual Americans need not be embarrassed any longer because of the antics of one dysfunctional person, but they do need to study the political process that allows degenerates, liars and thieves to claim the offices that guide our nation's destiny.<br>
When electing a President... more careful consideration must be given to who may succeed the President in the event he is no longer able to discharge his duties because of death or other circumstances.<br>
I cringe at the thought of what may follow Clinton's resignation or impeachment.  To me Al Gore epitomizes the adage that a politician's favorite color is plaid.  The man is hollow... and his embracement of the truth is highly questionable.. his behavior as Vice President is suspect, with his dealings with China and other &quot;fund&quot; raising activities... but he does wear nice ties.<br>
What ever happened to Norman Rockwell's America?  Just when did work ethic, diligent endeavor, morality, truth and courage fall into last place behind blasphemy, lies, laziness, sexual misconduct and greed?<br>
Something needs to be done at the polling booth before it is too late.  It is a slothful and degenerate nation that elects trash for its leadership.  Too few have paid the toughest price to protect our institutions, while too many disregard their sacredness.  Too many ticks will kill the host!<br><br>
We are on the threshold of a harsh dose of reality!  It's about time!! 
